89/*
90 * This is the header for map-format RBT images. It is populated,
91 * and then written, as the LAST thing done to the file before returning.
92 * Writing this last (with zeros in the header area initially) will ensure
93 * that the header is only valid when the RBT image is also valid.
94 */
95typedef struct file_header file_header_t;
96
97/* Pad to 32 bytes */
98static char FILE_VERSION[32] = "\0";
99
100/* Header length, always the same size regardless of structure size */
101#define HEADER_LENGTH 1024
102
103struct file_header {
104 char version1[32];
105 uint64_t first_node_offset; /* usually 1024 */
106 /*
107 * information about the system on which the map file was generated
108 * will be used to tell if we can load the map file or not
109 */
110 uint32_t ptrsize;
111 unsigned int bigendian:1; /* big or little endian system */
112 unsigned int rdataset_fixed:1; /* compiled with --enable-rrset-fixed */
113 unsigned int nodecount; /* shadow from rbt structure */
114 uint64_t crc;
115 char version2[32]; /* repeated; must match version1 */
116};

118/*
119 * The following declarations are for the serialization of an RBT:
120 *
121 * step one: write out a zeroed header of 1024 bytes
122 * step two: walk the tree in a depth-first, left-right-down order, writing
123 * out the nodes, reserving space as we go, correcting addresses to point
124 * at the proper offset in the file, and setting a flag for each pointer to
125 * indicate that it is a reference to a location in the file, rather than in
126 * memory.
127 * step three: write out the header, adding the information that will be
128 * needed to re-create the tree object itself.
129 *
130 * The RBTDB object will do this three times, once for each of the three
131 * RBT objects it contains.
132 *
133 * Note: 'file' must point an actual open file that can be mmapped
134 * and fseeked, not to a pipe or stream
135 */

206#define LEFT(node) ((node)->left)

212#define HASHNEXT(node) ((node)->hashnext)

215#define NAMELEN(node) ((node)->namelen)
216#define OLDNAMELEN(node) ((node)->oldnamelen)
217#define OFFSETLEN(node) ((node)->offsetlen)
218#define ATTRS(node) ((node)->attributes)
219#define IS_ROOT(node) ((node)->is_root)

223 * Structure elements from the rbtdb.c, not
224 * used as part of the rbt.c algorithms.

226#define DIRTY(node) ((node)->dirty)

230/*%
231 * The variable length stuff stored after the node has the following
232 * structure.
233 *
234 * &lt;name_data&gt;{1..255}&lt;oldoffsetlen&gt;{1}&lt;offsets&gt;{1..128}
235 *
236 * &lt;name_data&gt; contains the name of the node when it was created.
237 * &lt;oldoffsetlen&gt; contains the length of &lt;offsets&gt; when the node
238 * was created.
239 * &lt;offsets&gt; contains the offets into name for each label when the node
240 * was created.
241 */
242
243#define NAME(node) ((unsigned char *)((node) + 1))
244#define OFFSETS(node) (NAME(node) + OLDNAMELEN(node) + 1)
245#define OLDOFFSETLEN(node) (OFFSETS(node)[-1])
246
247#define NODE_SIZE(node) (sizeof(*node) + \
248 OLDNAMELEN(node) + OLDOFFSETLEN(node) + 1)
249
250/*%
251 * Color management.
252 */
253#define IS_RED(node) ((node) != NULL && (node)->color == RED)
254#define IS_BLACK(node) ((node) == NULL || (node)->color == BLACK)
255#define MAKE_RED(node) ((node)->color = RED)
256#define MAKE_BLACK(node) ((node)->color = BLACK)

258/*%
259 * Chain management.
260 *
261 * The "ancestors" member of chains were removed, with their job now
262 * being wholly handled by parent pointers (which didn't exist, because
263 * of memory concerns, when chains were first implemented).
264 */
265#define ADD_LEVEL(chain, node) \
266 do { \
267 INSIST((chain)->level_count < DNS_RBT_LEVELBLOCK); \
268 (chain)->levels[(chain)->level_count++] = (node); \
269 } while (0)

279 name->length = NAMELEN(node);
280 name->labels = OFFSETLEN(node);
281 name->ndata = NAME(node);
282 name->offsets = OFFSETS(node);
283 name->attributes = ATTRS(node);
284 name->attributes |= DNS_NAMEATTR_READONLY;
285}

319static void
320hexdump(const char *desc, void *blob, size_t size) {
321 char hexdump[BUFSIZ * 2 + 1];
322 isc_buffer_t b;
323 isc_region_t r;
324 isc_result_t result;
325 size_t bytes;
326 uint8_t *data = blob;
327
328 fprintf(stderr, "%s: ", desc);
329 do {
330 isc_buffer_init(&b, hexdump, sizeof(hexdump));
331 r.base = data;
332 r.length = bytes = (size > BUFSIZ) ? BUFSIZ : size;
333 result = isc_hex_totext(&r, 0, "", &b);
334 RUNTIME_CHECK(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
335 isc_buffer_putuint8(&b, 0);
336 fprintf(stderr, "%s", hexdump);
337 data += bytes;
338 size -= bytes;
339 } while (size > 0);
340 fprintf(stderr, "\n");
341}
342#endif /* DEBUG */

353static void
354fixup_uppernodes_helper(dns_rbtnode_t *node, dns_rbtnode_t *uppernode) {
355 if (node == NULL)
356 return;
357
358 UPPERNODE(node) = uppernode;
359
360 fixup_uppernodes_helper(LEFT(node), uppernode);
361 fixup_uppernodes_helper(RIGHT(node), uppernode);
362 fixup_uppernodes_helper(DOWN(node), node);
363}

374size_t
375dns__rbtnode_getdistance(dns_rbtnode_t *node) {
376 size_t nodes = 1;
377
378 while (node != NULL) {
379 if (IS_ROOT(node))
380 break;
381 nodes++;
382 node = PARENT(node);
383 }
384
385 return (nodes);
386}

434static isc_result_t
435dns_rbt_zero_header(FILE *file) {
436 /*
437 * Write out a zeroed header as a placeholder. Doing this ensures
438 * that the file will not read while it is partially written, should
439 * writing fail or be interrupted.
440 */
441 char buffer[HEADER_LENGTH];
442 isc_result_t result;
443
444 memset(buffer, 0, HEADER_LENGTH);
445 result = isc_stdio_write(buffer, 1, HEADER_LENGTH, file, NULL);
446 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
447 return (result);
448
449 result = fflush(file);
450 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
451 return (result);
452
453 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
454}

456static isc_once_t once = ISC_ONCE_INIT;

458static void
459init_file_version(void) {
460 int n;
461
462 memset(FILE_VERSION, 0, sizeof(FILE_VERSION));
463 n = snprintf(FILE_VERSION, sizeof(FILE_VERSION),
464 "RBT Image %s %s", dns_major, dns_mapapi);
465 INSIST(n > 0 && (unsigned int)n < sizeof(FILE_VERSION));
466}
467
468/*
469 * Write out the real header, including NodeDump version information
470 * and the offset of the first node.
471 *
472 * Any information stored in the rbt object itself should be stored
473 * here.
474 */
475static isc_result_t
476write_header(FILE *file, dns_rbt_t *rbt, uint64_t first_node_offset,
477 uint64_t crc)
478{
479 file_header_t header;
480 isc_result_t result;
481 off_t location;
482
483 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_once_do(&once, init_file_version) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
484
485 memset(&header, 0, sizeof(file_header_t));
486 memmove(header.version1, FILE_VERSION, sizeof(header.version1));
487 memmove(header.version2, FILE_VERSION, sizeof(header.version2));
488 header.first_node_offset = first_node_offset;
489 header.ptrsize = (uint32_t) sizeof(void *);
490 header.bigendian = (1 == htonl(1)) ? 1 : 0;
491
492#ifdef DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
493 header.rdataset_fixed = 1;
494#else
495 header.rdataset_fixed = 0;
496#endif
497
498 header.nodecount = rbt->nodecount;
499
500 header.crc = crc;
501
502 CHECK(isc_stdio_tell(file, &location));
503 location = dns_rbt_serialize_align(location);
504 CHECK(isc_stdio_seek(file, location, SEEK_SET));
505 CHECK(isc_stdio_write(&header, 1, sizeof(file_header_t), file, NULL));
506 CHECK(fflush(file));
507
508 /* Ensure we are always at the end of the file. */
509 CHECK(isc_stdio_seek(file, 0, SEEK_END));
510
511 cleanup:
512 return (result);
513}
514
515static bool
516match_header_version(file_header_t *header) {
517 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_once_do(&once, init_file_version) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
518
519 if (memcmp(header->version1, FILE_VERSION,
520 sizeof(header->version1)) != 0 ||
521 memcmp(header->version2, FILE_VERSION,
522 sizeof(header->version1)) != 0)
523 {
524 return (false);
525 }
526
527 return (true);
528}

530static isc_result_t
531serialize_node(FILE *file, dns_rbtnode_t *node, uintptr_t left,
532 uintptr_t right, uintptr_t down, uintptr_t parent,
533 uintptr_t data, uint64_t *crc)
534{
535 dns_rbtnode_t temp_node;
536 off_t file_position;
537 unsigned char *node_data;
538 size_t datasize;
539 isc_result_t result;
540#ifdef DEBUG
541 dns_name_t nodename;
542#endif
543
544 INSIST(node != NULL);
545
546 CHECK(isc_stdio_tell(file, &file_position));
547 file_position = dns_rbt_serialize_align(file_position);
548 CHECK(isc_stdio_seek(file, file_position, SEEK_SET));
549
550 temp_node = *node;
551 temp_node.down_is_relative = 0;
552 temp_node.left_is_relative = 0;
553 temp_node.right_is_relative = 0;
554 temp_node.parent_is_relative = 0;
555 temp_node.data_is_relative = 0;
556 temp_node.is_mmapped = 1;
557
558 /*
559 * If the next node is not NULL, calculate the next node's location
560 * in the file. Note that this will have to change when the data
561 * structure changes, and it also assumes that we always write the
562 * nodes out in list order (which we currently do.)
563 */
564 if (temp_node.parent != NULL) {
565 temp_node.parent = (dns_rbtnode_t *)(parent);
566 temp_node.parent_is_relative = 1;
567 }
568 if (temp_node.left != NULL) {
569 temp_node.left = (dns_rbtnode_t *)(left);
570 temp_node.left_is_relative = 1;
571 }
572 if (temp_node.right != NULL) {
573 temp_node.right = (dns_rbtnode_t *)(right);
574 temp_node.right_is_relative = 1;
575 }
576 if (temp_node.down != NULL) {
577 temp_node.down = (dns_rbtnode_t *)(down);
578 temp_node.down_is_relative = 1;
579 }
580 if (temp_node.data != NULL) {
581 temp_node.data = (dns_rbtnode_t *)(data);
582 temp_node.data_is_relative = 1;
583 }
584
585 node_data = (unsigned char *) node + sizeof(dns_rbtnode_t);
586 datasize = NODE_SIZE(node) - sizeof(dns_rbtnode_t);
587
588 CHECK(isc_stdio_write(&temp_node, 1, sizeof(dns_rbtnode_t),
589 file, NULL));
590 CHECK(isc_stdio_write(node_data, 1, datasize, file, NULL));
591
592#ifdef DEBUG
593 dns_name_init(&nodename, NULL);
594 NODENAME(node, &nodename);
595 fprintf(stderr, "serialize ");
596 dns_name_print(&nodename, stderr);
597 fprintf(stderr, "\n");
598 hexdump("node header", &temp_node,
599 sizeof(dns_rbtnode_t));
600 hexdump("node data", node_data, datasize);
601#endif
602
603 isc_crc64_update(crc, (const uint8_t *) &temp_node,
604 sizeof(dns_rbtnode_t));
605 isc_crc64_update(crc, (const uint8_t *) node_data, datasize);
606
607 cleanup:
608 return (result);
609}

611static isc_result_t
612serialize_nodes(FILE *file, dns_rbtnode_t *node, uintptr_t parent,
613 dns_rbtdatawriter_t datawriter, void *writer_arg,
614 uintptr_t *where, uint64_t *crc)
615{
616 uintptr_t left = 0, right = 0, down = 0, data = 0;
617 off_t location = 0, offset_adjust;
618 isc_result_t result;
619
620 if (node == NULL) {
621 if (where != NULL)
622 *where = 0;
623 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
624 }
625
626 /* Reserve space for current node. */
627 CHECK(isc_stdio_tell(file, &location));
628 location = dns_rbt_serialize_align(location);
629 CHECK(isc_stdio_seek(file, location, SEEK_SET));
630
631 offset_adjust = dns_rbt_serialize_align(location + NODE_SIZE(node));
632 CHECK(isc_stdio_seek(file, offset_adjust, SEEK_SET));
633
634 /*
635 * Serialize the rest of the tree.
636 *
637 * WARNING: A change in the order (from left, right, down)
638 * will break the way the crc hash is computed.
639 */
640 CHECK(serialize_nodes(file, getleft(node, NULL), location,
641 datawriter, writer_arg, &left, crc));
642 CHECK(serialize_nodes(file, getright(node, NULL), location,
643 datawriter, writer_arg, &right, crc));
644 CHECK(serialize_nodes(file, getdown(node, NULL), location,
645 datawriter, writer_arg, &down, crc));
646
647 if (node->data != NULL) {
648 off_t ret;
649
650 CHECK(isc_stdio_tell(file, &ret));
651 ret = dns_rbt_serialize_align(ret);
652 CHECK(isc_stdio_seek(file, ret, SEEK_SET));
653 data = ret;
654
655 datawriter(file, node->data, writer_arg, crc);
656 }
657
658 /* Seek back to reserved space. */
659 CHECK(isc_stdio_seek(file, location, SEEK_SET));
660
661 /* Serialize the current node. */
662 CHECK(serialize_node(file, node, left, right, down, parent, data, crc));
663
664 /* Ensure we are always at the end of the file. */
665 CHECK(isc_stdio_seek(file, 0, SEEK_END));
666
667 if (where != NULL)
668 *where = (uintptr_t) location;
669
670 cleanup:
671 return (result);
672}
673
674off_t
675dns_rbt_serialize_align(off_t target) {
676 off_t offset = target % 8;
677
678 if (offset == 0)
679 return (target);
680 else
681 return (target + 8 - offset);
682}

684isc_result_t
685dns_rbt_serialize_tree(FILE *file, dns_rbt_t *rbt,
686 dns_rbtdatawriter_t datawriter,
687 void *writer_arg, off_t *offset)
688{
689 isc_result_t result;
690 off_t header_position, node_position, end_position;
691 uint64_t crc;
692
693 REQUIRE(file != NULL);
694
695 CHECK(isc_file_isplainfilefd(fileno(file)));
696
697 isc_crc64_init(&crc);
698
699 CHECK(isc_stdio_tell(file, &header_position));
700
701 /* Write dummy header */
702 CHECK(dns_rbt_zero_header(file));
703
704 /* Serialize nodes */
705 CHECK(isc_stdio_tell(file, &node_position));
706 CHECK(serialize_nodes(file, rbt->root, 0, datawriter,
707 writer_arg, NULL, &crc));
708
709 CHECK(isc_stdio_tell(file, &end_position));
710 if (node_position == end_position) {
711 CHECK(isc_stdio_seek(file, header_position, SEEK_SET));
712 *offset = 0;
713 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
714 }
715
716 isc_crc64_final(&crc);
717#ifdef DEBUG
718 hexdump("serializing CRC", &crc, sizeof(crc));
719#endif
720
721 /* Serialize header */
722 CHECK(isc_stdio_seek(file, header_position, SEEK_SET));
723 CHECK(write_header(file, rbt, HEADER_LENGTH, crc));
724
725 /* Ensure we are always at the end of the file. */
726 CHECK(isc_stdio_seek(file, 0, SEEK_END));
727 *offset = dns_rbt_serialize_align(header_position);
728
729 cleanup:
730 return (result);
731}
732
733#define CONFIRM(a) do { \
734 if (! (a)) { \
735 result = ISC_R_INVALIDFILE; \
736 goto cleanup; \
737 } \
738} while(/*CONSTCOND*/0);
739
740static isc_result_t
741treefix(dns_rbt_t *rbt, void *base, size_t filesize, dns_rbtnode_t *n,
742 const dns_name_t *name, dns_rbtdatafixer_t datafixer,
743 void *fixer_arg, uint64_t *crc)
744{
745 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
746 dns_fixedname_t fixed;
747 dns_name_t nodename, *fullname;
748 unsigned char *node_data;
749 dns_rbtnode_t header;
750 size_t datasize, nodemax = filesize - sizeof(dns_rbtnode_t);
751
752 if (n == NULL)
753 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
754
755 CONFIRM((void *) n >= base);
756 CONFIRM((char *) n - (char *) base <= (int) nodemax);
757 CONFIRM(DNS_RBTNODE_VALID(n));
758
759 dns_name_init(&nodename, NULL);
760 NODENAME(n, &nodename);
761
762 fullname = &nodename;
763 CONFIRM(dns_name_isvalid(fullname));
764
765 if (!dns_name_isabsolute(&nodename)) {
766 fullname = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed);
767 CHECK(dns_name_concatenate(&nodename, name, fullname, NULL));
768 }
769
770 /* memorize header contents prior to fixup */
771 memmove(&header, n, sizeof(header));
772
773 if (n->left_is_relative) {
774 CONFIRM(n->left <= (dns_rbtnode_t *) nodemax);
775 n->left = getleft(n, rbt->mmap_location);
776 n->left_is_relative = 0;
777 CONFIRM(DNS_RBTNODE_VALID(n->left));
778 } else
779 CONFIRM(n->left == NULL);
780
781 if (n->right_is_relative) {
782 CONFIRM(n->right <= (dns_rbtnode_t *) nodemax);
783 n->right = getright(n, rbt->mmap_location);
784 n->right_is_relative = 0;
785 CONFIRM(DNS_RBTNODE_VALID(n->right));
786 } else
787 CONFIRM(n->right == NULL);
788
789 if (n->down_is_relative) {
790 CONFIRM(n->down <= (dns_rbtnode_t *) nodemax);
791 n->down = getdown(n, rbt->mmap_location);
792 n->down_is_relative = 0;
793 CONFIRM(n->down > (dns_rbtnode_t *) n);
794 CONFIRM(DNS_RBTNODE_VALID(n->down));
795 } else
796 CONFIRM(n->down == NULL);
797
798 if (n->parent_is_relative) {
799 CONFIRM(n->parent <= (dns_rbtnode_t *) nodemax);
800 n->parent = getparent(n, rbt->mmap_location);
801 n->parent_is_relative = 0;
802 CONFIRM(n->parent < (dns_rbtnode_t *) n);
803 CONFIRM(DNS_RBTNODE_VALID(n->parent));
804 } else
805 CONFIRM(n->parent == NULL);
806
807 if (n->data_is_relative) {
808 CONFIRM(n->data <= (void *) filesize);
809 n->data = getdata(n, rbt->mmap_location);
810 n->data_is_relative = 0;
811 CONFIRM(n->data > (void *) n);
812 } else
813 CONFIRM(n->data == NULL);
814
815 hash_node(rbt, n, fullname);
816
817 /* a change in the order (from left, right, down) will break hashing*/
818 if (n->left != NULL)
819 CHECK(treefix(rbt, base, filesize, n->left, name,
820 datafixer, fixer_arg, crc));
821 if (n->right != NULL)
822 CHECK(treefix(rbt, base, filesize, n->right, name,
823 datafixer, fixer_arg, crc));
824 if (n->down != NULL)
825 CHECK(treefix(rbt, base, filesize, n->down, fullname,
826 datafixer, fixer_arg, crc));
827
828 if (datafixer != NULL && n->data != NULL)
829 CHECK(datafixer(n, base, filesize, fixer_arg, crc));
830
831 rbt->nodecount++;
832 node_data = (unsigned char *) n + sizeof(dns_rbtnode_t);
833 datasize = NODE_SIZE(n) - sizeof(dns_rbtnode_t);
834
835#ifdef DEBUG
836 fprintf(stderr, "deserialize ");
837 dns_name_print(&nodename, stderr);
838 fprintf(stderr, "\n");
839 hexdump("node header", &header,
840 sizeof(dns_rbtnode_t));
841 hexdump("node data", node_data, datasize);
842#endif
843 isc_crc64_update(crc, (const uint8_t *) &header,
844 sizeof(dns_rbtnode_t));
845 isc_crc64_update(crc, (const uint8_t *) node_data,
846 datasize);
847
848 cleanup:
849 return (result);
850}
851
852isc_result_t
853dns_rbt_deserialize_tree(void *base_address, size_t filesize,
854 off_t header_offset, isc_mem_t *mctx,
855 dns_rbtdeleter_t deleter, void *deleter_arg,
856 dns_rbtdatafixer_t datafixer, void *fixer_arg,
857 dns_rbtnode_t **originp, dns_rbt_t **rbtp)
858{
859 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
860 file_header_t *header;
861 dns_rbt_t *rbt = NULL;
862 uint64_t crc;
863 unsigned int host_big_endian;
864
865 REQUIRE(originp == NULL || *originp == NULL);
866 REQUIRE(rbtp != NULL && *rbtp == NULL);
867
868 isc_crc64_init(&crc);
869
870 CHECK(dns_rbt_create(mctx, deleter, deleter_arg, &rbt));
871
872 rbt->mmap_location = base_address;
873
874 header = (file_header_t *)((char *)base_address + header_offset);
875 if (!match_header_version(header)) {
876 result = ISC_R_INVALIDFILE;
877 goto cleanup;
878 }
879
880#ifdef DNS_RDATASET_FIXED
881 if (header->rdataset_fixed != 1) {
882 result = ISC_R_INVALIDFILE;
883 goto cleanup;
884 }
885
886#else
887 if (header->rdataset_fixed != 0) {
888 result = ISC_R_INVALIDFILE;
889 goto cleanup;
890 }
891#endif
892
893 if (header->ptrsize != (uint32_t) sizeof(void *)) {
894 result = ISC_R_INVALIDFILE;
895 goto cleanup;
896 }
897
898 host_big_endian = (1 == htonl(1));
899 if (header->bigendian != host_big_endian) {
900 result = ISC_R_INVALIDFILE;
901 goto cleanup;
902 }
903
904 /* Copy other data items from the header into our rbt. */
905 rbt->root = (dns_rbtnode_t *)((char *)base_address +
906 header_offset + header->first_node_offset);
907
908 if ((header->nodecount * sizeof(dns_rbtnode_t)) > filesize) {
909 result = ISC_R_INVALIDFILE;
910 goto cleanup;
911 }
912 rehash(rbt, header->nodecount);
913
914 CHECK(treefix(rbt, base_address, filesize, rbt->root,
915 dns_rootname, datafixer, fixer_arg, &crc));
916
917 isc_crc64_final(&crc);
918#ifdef DEBUG
919 hexdump("deserializing CRC", &crc, sizeof(crc));
920#endif
921
922 /* Check file hash */
923 if (header->crc != crc) {
924 result = ISC_R_INVALIDFILE;
925 goto cleanup;
926 }
927
928 if (header->nodecount != rbt->nodecount) {
929 result = ISC_R_INVALIDFILE;
930 goto cleanup;
931 }
932
933 fixup_uppernodes(rbt);
934
935 *rbtp = rbt;
936 if (originp != NULL)
937 *originp = rbt->root;
938
939 cleanup:
940 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS && rbt != NULL) {
941 rbt->root = NULL;
942 rbt->nodecount = 0;
943 dns_rbt_destroy(&rbt);
944 }
945
946 return (result);
947}

949/*
950 * Initialize a red/black tree of trees.
951 */
952isc_result_t
953dns_rbt_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_rbtdeleter_t deleter,
954 void *deleter_arg, dns_rbt_t **rbtp)
955{
956 isc_result_t result;
957 dns_rbt_t *rbt;
958
959 REQUIRE(mctx != NULL);
960 REQUIRE(rbtp != NULL && *rbtp == NULL);
961 REQUIRE(deleter == NULL ? deleter_arg == NULL : 1);
962
963 rbt = (dns_rbt_t *)isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(*rbt));
964 if (rbt == NULL)
965 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
966
967 rbt->mctx = NULL;
968 isc_mem_attach(mctx, &rbt->mctx);
969 rbt->data_deleter = deleter;
970 rbt->deleter_arg = deleter_arg;
971 rbt->root = NULL;
972 rbt->nodecount = 0;
973 rbt->hashtable = NULL;
974 rbt->hashsize = 0;
975 rbt->mmap_location = NULL;
976
977 result = inithash(rbt);
978 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
979 isc_mem_putanddetach(&rbt->mctx, rbt, sizeof(*rbt));
980 return (result);
981 }
982
983 rbt->magic = RBT_MAGIC;
984
985 *rbtp = rbt;
986
987 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
988}

991 * Deallocate a red/black tree of trees.
992 */
993void
994dns_rbt_destroy(dns_rbt_t **rbtp) {
995 RUNTIME_CHECK(dns_rbt_destroy2(rbtp, 0) == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
996}

998isc_result_t
999dns_rbt_destroy2(dns_rbt_t **rbtp, unsigned int quantum) {
1000 dns_rbt_t *rbt;
1001
1002 REQUIRE(rbtp != NULL && VALID_RBT(*rbtp));
1003
1004 rbt = *rbtp;
1005
1006 deletetreeflat(rbt, quantum, false, &rbt->root);
1007 if (rbt->root != NULL)
1008 return (ISC_R_QUOTA);
1009
1010 INSIST(rbt->nodecount == 0);
1011
1012 rbt->mmap_location = NULL;
1013
1014 if (rbt->hashtable != NULL)
1015 isc_mem_put(rbt->mctx, rbt->hashtable,
1016 rbt->hashsize * sizeof(dns_rbtnode_t *));
1017
1018 rbt->magic = 0;
1019
1020 isc_mem_putanddetach(&rbt->mctx, rbt, sizeof(*rbt));
1021 *rbtp = NULL;
1022 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1023}

1041static inline isc_result_t
1042chain_name(dns_rbtnodechain_t *chain, dns_name_t *name,
1043 bool include_chain_end)
1044{
1045 dns_name_t nodename;
1046 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
1047 int i;
1048
1049 dns_name_init(&nodename, NULL);
1050
1051 if (include_chain_end && chain->end != NULL) {
1052 NODENAME(chain->end, &nodename);
1053 result = dns_name_copy(&nodename, name, NULL);
1054 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1055 return (result);
1056 } else
1057 dns_name_reset(name);
1058
1059 for (i = (int)chain->level_count - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
1060 NODENAME(chain->levels[i], &nodename);
1061 result = dns_name_concatenate(name, &nodename, name, NULL);
1062
1063 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1064 return (result);
1065 }
1066 return (result);
1067}
1068
1069static inline isc_result_t
1070move_chain_to_last(dns_rbtnodechain_t *chain, dns_rbtnode_t *node) {
1071 do {
1072 /*
1073 * Go as far right and then down as much as possible,
1074 * as long as the rightmost node has a down pointer.
1075 */
1076 while (RIGHT(node) != NULL)
1077 node = RIGHT(node);
1078
1079 if (DOWN(node) == NULL)
1080 break;
1081
1082 ADD_LEVEL(chain, node);
1083 node = DOWN(node);
1084 } while (1);
1085
1086 chain->end = node;
1087
1088 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1089}

1091/*
1092 * Add 'name' to tree, initializing its data pointer with 'data'.
1093 */
1094
1095isc_result_t
1096dns_rbt_addnode(dns_rbt_t *rbt, const dns_name_t *name, dns_rbtnode_t **nodep) {
1097 /*
1098 * Does this thing have too many variables or what?
1099 */
1100 dns_rbtnode_t **root, *parent, *child, *current, *new_current;
1101 dns_name_t *add_name, *new_name, current_name, *prefix, *suffix;
1102 dns_fixedname_t fixedcopy, fixedprefix, fixedsuffix, fnewname;
1103 dns_offsets_t current_offsets;
1104 dns_namereln_t compared;
1105 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
1106 unsigned int level_count;
1107 unsigned int common_labels;
1108 unsigned int nlabels, hlabels;
1109 int order;
1110
1111 REQUIRE(VALID_RBT(rbt));
1112 REQUIRE(dns_name_isabsolute(name));
1113 REQUIRE(nodep != NULL && *nodep == NULL);
1114
1115 /*
1116 * Dear future BIND developer,
1117 *
1118 * After you have tried attempting to optimize this routine by
1119 * using the hashtable and have realized your folly, please
1120 * append another cross ("X") below as a warning to the next
1121 * future BIND developer:
1122 *
1123 * Number of victim developers: X
1124 *
1125 * I wish the past developer had included such a notice.
1126 *
1127 * Long form: Unlike dns_rbt_findnode(), this function does not
1128 * lend itself to be optimized using the hashtable:
1129 *
1130 * 1. In the subtree where the insertion occurs, this function
1131 * needs to have the insertion point and the order where the
1132 * lookup terminated (i.e., at the insertion point where left or
1133 * right child is NULL). This cannot be determined from the
1134 * hashtable, so at least in that subtree, a BST O(log N) lookup
1135 * is necessary.
1136 *
1137 * 2. Our RBT nodes contain not only single labels but label
1138 * sequences to optimize space usage. So at every level, we have
1139 * to look for a match in the hashtable for all superdomains in
1140 * the rest of the name we're searching. This is an O(N)
1141 * operation at least, here N being the label size of name, each
1142 * of which is a hashtable lookup involving dns_name_equal()
1143 * comparisons.
1144 */
1145
1146 /*
1147 * Create a copy of the name so the original name structure is
1148 * not modified.
1149 */
1150 add_name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixedcopy);
1151 INSIST(add_name != NULL);
1152 dns_name_clone(name, add_name);
1153
1154 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(rbt->root == NULL)) {
1155 result = create_node(rbt->mctx, add_name, &new_current);
1156 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1157 rbt->nodecount++;
1158 new_current->is_root = 1;
1159
1160 UPPERNODE(new_current) = NULL;
1161
1162 rbt->root = new_current;
1163 *nodep = new_current;
1164 hash_node(rbt, new_current, name);
1165 }
1166 return (result);
1167 }
1168
1169 level_count = 0;
1170
1171 prefix = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixedprefix);
1172 suffix = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixedsuffix);
1173
1174 INSIST(prefix != NULL);
1175 INSIST(suffix != NULL);
1176
1177 root = &rbt->root;
1178 INSIST(IS_ROOT(*root));
1179 parent = NULL;
1180 current = NULL;
1181 child = *root;
1182 dns_name_init(&current_name, current_offsets);
1183 new_name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fnewname);
1184 nlabels = dns_name_countlabels(name);
1185 hlabels = 0;
1186
1187 do {
1188 current = child;
1189
1190 NODENAME(current, &current_name);
1191 compared = dns_name_fullcompare(add_name, &current_name,
1192 &order, &common_labels);
1193
1194 if (compared == dns_namereln_equal) {
1195 *nodep = current;
1196 result = ISC_R_EXISTS;
1197 break;
1198
1199 }
1200
1201 if (compared == dns_namereln_none) {
1202
1203 if (order < 0) {
1204 parent = current;
1205 child = LEFT(current);
1206
1207 } else if (order > 0) {
1208 parent = current;
1209 child = RIGHT(current);
1210
1211 }
1212
1213 } else {
1214 /*
1215 * This name has some suffix in common with the
1216 * name at the current node. If the name at
1217 * the current node is shorter, that means the
1218 * new name should be in a subtree. If the
1219 * name at the current node is longer, that means
1220 * the down pointer to this tree should point
1221 * to a new tree that has the common suffix, and
1222 * the non-common parts of these two names should
1223 * start a new tree.
1224 */
1225 hlabels += common_labels;
1226 if (compared == dns_namereln_subdomain) {
1227 /*
1228 * All of the existing labels are in common,
1229 * so the new name is in a subtree.
1230 * Whack off the common labels for the
1231 * not-in-common part to be searched for
1232 * in the next level.
1233 */
1234 dns_name_split(add_name, common_labels,
1235 add_name, NULL);
1236
1237 /*
1238 * Follow the down pointer (possibly NULL).
1239 */
1240 root = &DOWN(current);
1241
1242 INSIST(*root == NULL ||
1243 (IS_ROOT(*root) &&
1244 PARENT(*root) == current));
1245
1246 parent = NULL;
1247 child = DOWN(current);
1248
1249 INSIST(level_count < DNS_RBT_LEVELBLOCK);
1250 level_count++;
1251 } else {
1252 /*
1253 * The number of labels in common is fewer
1254 * than the number of labels at the current
1255 * node, so the current node must be adjusted
1256 * to have just the common suffix, and a down
1257 * pointer made to a new tree.
1258 */
1259
1260 INSIST(compared == dns_namereln_commonancestor
1261 || compared == dns_namereln_contains);
1262
1263 /*
1264 * Ensure the number of levels in the tree
1265 * does not exceed the number of logical
1266 * levels allowed by DNSSEC.
1267 *
1268 * XXXDCL need a better error result?
1269 */
1270 if (level_count >= DNS_RBT_LEVELBLOCK) {
1271 result = ISC_R_NOSPACE;
1272 break;
1273 }
1274
1275 /*
1276 * Split the name into two parts, a prefix
1277 * which is the not-in-common parts of the
1278 * two names and a suffix that is the common
1279 * parts of them.
1280 */
1281 dns_name_split(&current_name, common_labels,
1282 prefix, suffix);
1283 result = create_node(rbt->mctx, suffix,
1284 &new_current);
1285
1286 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1287 break;
1288
1289 /*
1290 * Reproduce the tree attributes of the
1291 * current node.
1292 */
1293 new_current->is_root = current->is_root;
1294 if (current->nsec == DNS_RBT_NSEC_HAS_NSEC)
1295 new_current->nsec = DNS_RBT_NSEC_NORMAL;
1296 else
1297 new_current->nsec = current->nsec;
1298 PARENT(new_current) = PARENT(current);
1299 LEFT(new_current) = LEFT(current);
1300 RIGHT(new_current) = RIGHT(current);
1301 COLOR(new_current) = COLOR(current);
1302
1303 /*
1304 * Fix pointers that were to the current node.
1305 */
1306 if (parent != NULL) {
1307 if (LEFT(parent) == current)
1308 LEFT(parent) = new_current;
1309 else
1310 RIGHT(parent) = new_current;
1311 }
1312 if (LEFT(new_current) != NULL)
1313 PARENT(LEFT(new_current)) =
1314 new_current;
1315 if (RIGHT(new_current) != NULL)
1316 PARENT(RIGHT(new_current)) =
1317 new_current;
1318 if (*root == current)
1319 *root = new_current;
1320
1321 NAMELEN(current) = prefix->length;
1322 OFFSETLEN(current) = prefix->labels;
1323
1324 /*
1325 * Set up the new root of the next level.
1326 * By definition it will not be the top
1327 * level tree, so clear DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE.
1328 */
1329 current->is_root = 1;
1330 PARENT(current) = new_current;
1331 DOWN(new_current) = current;
1332 root = &DOWN(new_current);
1333
1334 UPPERNODE(new_current) = UPPERNODE(current);
1335 UPPERNODE(current) = new_current;
1336
1337 INSIST(level_count < DNS_RBT_LEVELBLOCK);
1338 level_count++;
1339
1340 LEFT(current) = NULL;
1341 RIGHT(current) = NULL;
1342
1343 MAKE_BLACK(current);
1344 ATTRS(current) &= ~DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE;
1345
1346 rbt->nodecount++;
1347 dns_name_getlabelsequence(name,
1348 nlabels - hlabels,
1349 hlabels, new_name);
1350 hash_node(rbt, new_current, new_name);
1351
1352 if (common_labels ==
1353 dns_name_countlabels(add_name)) {
1354 /*
1355 * The name has been added by pushing
1356 * the not-in-common parts down to
1357 * a new level.
1358 */
1359 *nodep = new_current;
1360 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1361
1362 } else {
1363 /*
1364 * The current node has no data,
1365 * because it is just a placeholder.
1366 * Its data pointer is already NULL
1367 * from create_node()), so there's
1368 * nothing more to do to it.
1369 */
1370
1371 /*
1372 * The not-in-common parts of the new
1373 * name will be inserted into the new
1374 * level following this loop (unless
1375 * result != ISC_R_SUCCESS, which
1376 * is tested after the loop ends).
1377 */
1378 dns_name_split(add_name, common_labels,
1379 add_name, NULL);
1380
1381 break;
1382 }
1383
1384 }
1385
1386 }
1387
1388 } while (ISC_LIKELY(child != NULL));
1389
1390 if (ISC_LIKELY(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS))
1391 result = create_node(rbt->mctx, add_name, &new_current);
1392
1393 if (ISC_LIKELY(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)) {
1394 if (*root == NULL) {
1395 UPPERNODE(new_current) = current;
1396 } else {
1397 UPPERNODE(new_current) = PARENT(*root);
1398 }
1399
1400 addonlevel(new_current, current, order, root);
1401 rbt->nodecount++;
1402 *nodep = new_current;
1403 hash_node(rbt, new_current, name);
1404 }
1405
1406 return (result);
1407}

1409/*
1410 * Add a name to the tree of trees, associating it with some data.
1411 */
1412isc_result_t
1413dns_rbt_addname(dns_rbt_t *rbt, const dns_name_t *name, void *data) {
1414 isc_result_t result;
1415 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
1416
1417 REQUIRE(VALID_RBT(rbt));
1418 REQUIRE(dns_name_isabsolute(name));
1419
1420 node = NULL;
1421
1422 result = dns_rbt_addnode(rbt, name, &node);
1423
1424 /*
1425 * dns_rbt_addnode will report the node exists even when
1426 * it does not have data associated with it, but the
1427 * dns_rbt_*name functions all behave depending on whether
1428 * there is data associated with a node.
1429 */
1430 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS ||
1431 (result == ISC_R_EXISTS && DATA(node) == NULL)) {
1432 DATA(node) = data;
1433 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
1434 }
1435
1436 return (result);
1437}

1439/*
1440 * Find the node for "name" in the tree of trees.
1441 */
1442isc_result_t
1443dns_rbt_findnode(dns_rbt_t *rbt, const dns_name_t *name, dns_name_t *foundname,
1444 dns_rbtnode_t **node, dns_rbtnodechain_t *chain,
1445 unsigned int options, dns_rbtfindcallback_t callback,
1446 void *callback_arg)
1447{
1448 dns_rbtnode_t *current, *last_compared;
1449 dns_rbtnodechain_t localchain;
1450 dns_name_t *search_name, current_name, *callback_name;
1451 dns_fixedname_t fixedcallbackname, fixedsearchname;
1452 dns_namereln_t compared;
1453 isc_result_t result, saved_result;
1454 unsigned int common_labels;
1455 unsigned int hlabels = 0;
1456 int order;
1457
1458 REQUIRE(VALID_RBT(rbt));
1459 REQUIRE(dns_name_isabsolute(name));
1460 REQUIRE(node != NULL && *node == NULL);
1461 REQUIRE((options & (DNS_RBTFIND_NOEXACT | DNS_RBTFIND_NOPREDECESSOR))
1462 != (DNS_RBTFIND_NOEXACT | DNS_RBTFIND_NOPREDECESSOR));
1463
1464 /*
1465 * If there is a chain it needs to appear to be in a sane state,
1466 * otherwise a chain is still needed to generate foundname and
1467 * callback_name.
1468 */
1469 if (chain == NULL) {
1470 options |= DNS_RBTFIND_NOPREDECESSOR;
1471 chain = &localchain;
1472 dns_rbtnodechain_init(chain, rbt->mctx);
1473 } else
1474 dns_rbtnodechain_reset(chain);
1475
1476 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(rbt->root == NULL))
1477 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
1478
1479 /*
1480 * Appease GCC about variables it incorrectly thinks are
1481 * possibly used uninitialized.
1482 */
1483 compared = dns_namereln_none;
1484 last_compared = NULL;
1485 order = 0;
1486
1487 callback_name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixedcallbackname);
1488
1489 /*
1490 * search_name is the name segment being sought in each tree level.
1491 * By using a fixedname, the search_name will definitely have offsets
1492 * for use by any splitting.
1493 * By using dns_name_clone, no name data should be copied thanks to
1494 * the lack of bitstring labels.
1495 */
1496 search_name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixedsearchname);
1497 INSIST(search_name != NULL);
1498 dns_name_clone(name, search_name);
1499
1500 dns_name_init(&current_name, NULL);
1501
1502 saved_result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
1503 current = rbt->root;
1504
1505 while (ISC_LIKELY(current != NULL)) {
1506 NODENAME(current, &current_name);
1507 compared = dns_name_fullcompare(search_name, &current_name,
1508 &order, &common_labels);
1509 /*
1510 * last_compared is used as a shortcut to start (or
1511 * continue rather) finding the stop-node of the search
1512 * when hashing was used (see much below in this
1513 * function).
1514 */
1515 last_compared = current;
1516
1517 if (compared == dns_namereln_equal)
1518 break;
1519
1520 if (compared == dns_namereln_none) {
1521 /*
1522 * Here, current is pointing at a subtree root
1523 * node. We try to find a matching node using
1524 * the hashtable. We can get one of 3 results
1525 * here: (a) we locate the matching node, (b) we
1526 * find a node to which the current node has a
1527 * subdomain relation, (c) we fail to find (a)
1528 * or (b).
1529 */
1530
1531 dns_name_t hash_name;
1532 dns_rbtnode_t *hnode;
1533 dns_rbtnode_t *up_current;
1534 unsigned int nlabels;
1535 unsigned int tlabels = 1;
1536 unsigned int hash;
1537
1538 /*
1539 * The case of current not being a subtree root,
1540 * that means a left or right pointer was
1541 * followed, only happens when the algorithm
1542 * fell through to the traditional binary search
1543 * because of a bitstring label. Since we
1544 * dropped the bitstring support, this should
1545 * not happen.
1546 */
1547 INSIST(IS_ROOT(current));
1548
1549 nlabels = dns_name_countlabels(search_name);
1550
1551 /*
1552 * current is the root of the current level, so
1553 * its parent is the same as its "up" pointer.
1554 */
1555 up_current = PARENT(current);
1556 dns_name_init(&hash_name, NULL);
1557
1558 hashagain:
1559 /*
1560 * Compute the hash over the full absolute
1561 * name. Look for the smallest suffix match at
1562 * this tree level (hlevel), and then at every
1563 * iteration, look for the next smallest suffix
1564 * match (add another subdomain label to the
1565 * absolute name being hashed).
1566 */
1567 dns_name_getlabelsequence(name,
1568 nlabels - tlabels,
1569 hlabels + tlabels,
1570 &hash_name);
1571 hash = dns_name_fullhash(&hash_name, false);
1572 dns_name_getlabelsequence(search_name,
1573 nlabels - tlabels,
1574 tlabels, &hash_name);
1575
1576 /*
1577 * Walk all the nodes in the hash bucket pointed
1578 * by the computed hash value.
1579 */
1580 for (hnode = rbt->hashtable[hash % rbt->hashsize];
1581 hnode != NULL;
1582 hnode = hnode->hashnext)
1583 {
1584 dns_name_t hnode_name;
1585
1586 if (ISC_LIKELY(hash != HASHVAL(hnode)))
1587 continue;
1588 /*
1589 * This checks that the hashed label
1590 * sequence being looked up is at the
1591 * same tree level, so that we don't
1592 * match a labelsequence from some other
1593 * subdomain.
1594 */
1595 if (ISC_LIKELY(get_upper_node(hnode) !=
1596 up_current))
1597 {
1598 continue;
1599 }
1600
1601 dns_name_init(&hnode_name, NULL);
1602 NODENAME(hnode, &hnode_name);
1603 if (ISC_LIKELY(dns_name_equal(&hnode_name,
1604 &hash_name)))
1605 {
1606 break;
1607 }
1608 }
1609
1610 if (hnode != NULL) {
1611 current = hnode;
1612 /*
1613 * This is an optimization. If hashing found
1614 * the right node, the next call to
1615 * dns_name_fullcompare() would obviously
1616 * return _equal or _subdomain. Determine
1617 * which of those would be the case by
1618 * checking if the full name was hashed. Then
1619 * make it look like dns_name_fullcompare
1620 * was called and jump to the right place.
1621 */
1622 if (tlabels == nlabels) {
1623 compared = dns_namereln_equal;
1624 break;
1625 } else {
1626 common_labels = tlabels;
1627 compared = dns_namereln_subdomain;
1628 goto subdomain;
1629 }
1630 }
1631
1632 if (tlabels++ < nlabels)
1633 goto hashagain;
1634
1635 /*
1636 * All of the labels have been tried against the hash
1637 * table. Since we dropped the support of bitstring
1638 * labels, the name isn't in the table.
1639 */
1640 current = NULL;
1641 continue;
1642 } else {
1643 /*
1644 * The names have some common suffix labels.
1645 *
1646 * If the number in common are equal in length to
1647 * the current node's name length, then follow the
1648 * down pointer and search in the new tree.
1649 */
1650 if (compared == dns_namereln_subdomain) {
1651 subdomain:
1652 /*
1653 * Whack off the current node's common parts
1654 * for the name to search in the next level.
1655 */
1656 dns_name_split(search_name, common_labels,
1657 search_name, NULL);
1658 hlabels += common_labels;
1659 /*
1660 * This might be the closest enclosing name.
1661 */
1662 if (DATA(current) != NULL ||
1663 (options & DNS_RBTFIND_EMPTYDATA) != 0)
1664 *node = current;
1665
1666 /*
1667 * Point the chain to the next level. This
1668 * needs to be done before 'current' is pointed
1669 * there because the callback in the next
1670 * block of code needs the current 'current',
1671 * but in the event the callback requests that
1672 * the search be stopped then the
1673 * DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH code at the end of this
1674 * function needs the chain pointed to the
1675 * next level.
1676 */
1677 ADD_LEVEL(chain, current);
1678
1679 /*
1680 * The caller may want to interrupt the
1681 * downward search when certain special nodes
1682 * are traversed. If this is a special node,
1683 * the callback is used to learn what the
1684 * caller wants to do.
1685 */
1686 if (callback != NULL &&
1687 FINDCALLBACK(current)) {
1688 result = chain_name(chain,
1689 callback_name,
1690 false);
1691 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1692 dns_rbtnodechain_reset(chain);
1693 return (result);
1694 }
1695
1696 result = (callback)(current,
1697 callback_name,
1698 callback_arg);
1699 if (result != DNS_R_CONTINUE) {
1700 saved_result = result;
1701 /*
1702 * Treat this node as if it
1703 * had no down pointer.
1704 */
1705 current = NULL;
1706 break;
1707 }
1708 }
1709
1710 /*
1711 * Finally, head to the next tree level.
1712 */
1713 current = DOWN(current);
1714 } else {
1715 /*
1716 * Though there are labels in common, the
1717 * entire name at this node is not common
1718 * with the search name so the search
1719 * name does not exist in the tree.
1720 */
1721 INSIST(compared == dns_namereln_commonancestor
1722 || compared == dns_namereln_contains);
1723
1724 current = NULL;
1725 }
1726 }
1727 }
1728
1729 /*
1730 * If current is not NULL, NOEXACT is not disallowing exact matches,
1731 * and either the node has data or an empty node is ok, return
1732 * ISC_R_SUCCESS to indicate an exact match.
1733 */
1734 if (current != NULL && (options & DNS_RBTFIND_NOEXACT) == 0 &&
1735 (DATA(current) != NULL ||
1736 (options & DNS_RBTFIND_EMPTYDATA) != 0)) {
1737 /*
1738 * Found an exact match.
1739 */
1740 chain->end = current;
1741 chain->level_matches = chain->level_count;
1742
1743 if (foundname != NULL)
1744 result = chain_name(chain, foundname, true);
1745 else
1746 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
1747
1748 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1749 *node = current;
1750 result = saved_result;
1751 } else
1752 *node = NULL;
1753 } else {
1754 /*
1755 * Did not find an exact match (or did not want one).
1756 */
1757 if (*node != NULL) {
1758 /*
1759 * ... but found a partially matching superdomain.
1760 * Unwind the chain to the partial match node
1761 * to set level_matches to the level above the node,
1762 * and then to derive the name.
1763 *
1764 * chain->level_count is guaranteed to be at least 1
1765 * here because by definition of finding a superdomain,
1766 * the chain is pointed to at least the first subtree.
1767 */
1768 chain->level_matches = chain->level_count - 1;
1769
1770 while (chain->levels[chain->level_matches] != *node) {
1771 INSIST(chain->level_matches > 0);
1772 chain->level_matches--;
1773 }
1774
1775 if (foundname != NULL) {
1776 unsigned int saved_count = chain->level_count;
1777
1778 chain->level_count = chain->level_matches + 1;
1779
1780 result = chain_name(chain, foundname,
1781 false);
1782
1783 chain->level_count = saved_count;
1784 } else
1785 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
1786
1787 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1788 result = DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH;
1789
1790 } else
1791 result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
1792
1793 if (current != NULL) {
1794 /*
1795 * There was an exact match but either
1796 * DNS_RBTFIND_NOEXACT was set, or
1797 * DNS_RBTFIND_EMPTYDATA was set and the node had no
1798 * data. A policy decision was made to set the
1799 * chain to the exact match, but this is subject
1800 * to change if it becomes apparent that something
1801 * else would be more useful. It is important that
1802 * this case is handled here, because the predecessor
1803 * setting code below assumes the match was not exact.
1804 */
1805 INSIST(((options & DNS_RBTFIND_NOEXACT) != 0) ||
1806 ((options & DNS_RBTFIND_EMPTYDATA) == 0 &&
1807 DATA(current) == NULL));
1808 chain->end = current;
1809
1810 } else if ((options & DNS_RBTFIND_NOPREDECESSOR) != 0) {
1811 /*
1812 * Ensure the chain points nowhere.
1813 */
1814 chain->end = NULL;
1815
1816 } else {
1817 /*
1818 * Since there was no exact match, the chain argument
1819 * needs to be pointed at the DNSSEC predecessor of
1820 * the search name.
1821 */
1822 if (compared == dns_namereln_subdomain) {
1823 /*
1824 * Attempted to follow a down pointer that was
1825 * NULL, which means the searched for name was
1826 * a subdomain of a terminal name in the tree.
1827 * Since there are no existing subdomains to
1828 * order against, the terminal name is the
1829 * predecessor.
1830 */
1831 INSIST(chain->level_count > 0);
1832 INSIST(chain->level_matches <
1833 chain->level_count);
1834 chain->end =
1835 chain->levels[--chain->level_count];
1836
1837 } else {
1838 isc_result_t result2;
1839
1840 /*
1841 * Point current to the node that stopped
1842 * the search.
1843 *
1844 * With the hashing modification that has been
1845 * added to the algorithm, the stop node of a
1846 * standard binary search is not known. So it
1847 * has to be found. There is probably a more
1848 * clever way of doing this.
1849 *
1850 * The assignment of current to NULL when
1851 * the relationship is *not* dns_namereln_none,
1852 * even though it later gets set to the same
1853 * last_compared anyway, is simply to not push
1854 * the while loop in one more level of
1855 * indentation.
1856 */
1857 if (compared == dns_namereln_none)
1858 current = last_compared;
1859 else
1860 current = NULL;
1861
1862 while (current != NULL) {
1863 NODENAME(current, &current_name);
1864 compared = dns_name_fullcompare(
1865 search_name,
1866 &current_name,
1867 &order,
1868 &common_labels);
1869 POST(compared);
1870
1871 last_compared = current;
1872
1873 /*
1874 * Standard binary search movement.
1875 */
1876 if (order < 0)
1877 current = LEFT(current);
1878 else
1879 current = RIGHT(current);
1880
1881 }
1882
1883 current = last_compared;
1884
1885 /*
1886 * Reached a point within a level tree that
1887 * positively indicates the name is not
1888 * present, but the stop node could be either
1889 * less than the desired name (order > 0) or
1890 * greater than the desired name (order < 0).
1891 *
1892 * If the stop node is less, it is not
1893 * necessarily the predecessor. If the stop
1894 * node has a down pointer, then the real
1895 * predecessor is at the end of a level below
1896 * (not necessarily the next level).
1897 * Move down levels until the rightmost node
1898 * does not have a down pointer.
1899 *
1900 * When the stop node is greater, it is
1901 * the successor. All the logic for finding
1902 * the predecessor is handily encapsulated
1903 * in dns_rbtnodechain_prev. In the event
1904 * that the search name is less than anything
1905 * else in the tree, the chain is reset.
1906 * XXX DCL What is the best way for the caller
1907 * to know that the search name has
1908 * no predecessor?
1909 */
1910
1911
1912 if (order > 0) {
1913 if (DOWN(current) != NULL) {
1914 ADD_LEVEL(chain, current);
1915
1916 result2 =
1917 move_chain_to_last(chain,
1918 DOWN(current));
1919
1920 if (result2 != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1921 result = result2;
1922 } else
1923 /*
1924 * Ah, the pure and simple
1925 * case. The stop node is the
1926 * predecessor.
1927 */
1928 chain->end = current;
1929
1930 } else {
1931 INSIST(order < 0);
1932
1933 chain->end = current;
1934
1935 result2 = dns_rbtnodechain_prev(chain,
1936 NULL,
1937 NULL);
1938 if (result2 == ISC_R_SUCCESS ||
1939 result2 == DNS_R_NEWORIGIN)
1940 ; /* Nothing. */
1941 else if (result2 == ISC_R_NOMORE)
1942 /*
1943 * There is no predecessor.
1944 */
1945 dns_rbtnodechain_reset(chain);
1946 else
1947 result = result2;
1948 }
1949
1950 }
1951 }
1952 }
1953
1954 ENSURE(*node == NULL || DNS_RBTNODE_VALID(*node));
1955
1956 return (result);
1957}

1982/*
1983 * Delete a name from the tree of trees.
1984 */
1985isc_result_t
1986dns_rbt_deletename(dns_rbt_t *rbt, const dns_name_t *name,
1987 bool recurse)
1988{
1989 dns_rbtnode_t *node = NULL;
1990 isc_result_t result;
1991
1992 REQUIRE(VALID_RBT(rbt));
1993 REQUIRE(dns_name_isabsolute(name));
1994
1995 /*
1996 * First, find the node.
1997 *
1998 * When searching, the name might not have an exact match:
1999 * consider a.b.a.com, b.b.a.com and c.b.a.com as the only
2000 * elements of a tree, which would make layer 1 a single
2001 * node tree of "b.a.com" and layer 2 a three node tree of
2002 * a, b, and c. Deleting a.com would find only a partial depth
2003 * match in the first layer. Should it be a requirement that
2004 * that the name to be deleted have data? For now, it is.
2005 *
2006 * ->dirty, ->locknum and ->references are ignored; they are
2007 * solely the province of rbtdb.c.
2008 */
2009 result = dns_rbt_findnode(rbt, name, NULL, &node, NULL,
2010 DNS_RBTFIND_NOOPTIONS, NULL, NULL);
2011
2012 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2013 if (DATA(node) != NULL)
2014 result = dns_rbt_deletenode(rbt, node, recurse);
2015 else
2016 result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
2017
2018 } else if (result == DNS_R_PARTIALMATCH)
2019 result = ISC_R_NOTFOUND;
2020
2021 return (result);
2022}
2023
2024/*
2025 * Remove a node from the tree of trees.
2026 *
2027 * NOTE WELL: deletion is *not* symmetric with addition; that is, reversing
2028 * a sequence of additions to be deletions will not generally get the
2029 * tree back to the state it started in. For example, if the addition
2030 * of "b.c" caused the node "a.b.c" to be split, pushing "a" to its own level,
2031 * then the subsequent deletion of "b.c" will not cause "a" to be pulled up,
2032 * restoring "a.b.c". The RBT *used* to do this kind of rejoining, but it
2033 * turned out to be a bad idea because it could corrupt an active nodechain
2034 * that had "b.c" as one of its levels -- and the RBT has no idea what
2035 * nodechains are in use by callers, so it can't even *try* to helpfully
2036 * fix them up (which would probably be doomed to failure anyway).
2037 *
2038 * Similarly, it is possible to leave the tree in a state where a supposedly
2039 * deleted node still exists. The first case of this is obvious; take
2040 * the tree which has "b.c" on one level, pointing to "a". Now deleted "b.c".
2041 * It was just established in the previous paragraph why we can't pull "a"
2042 * back up to its parent level. But what happens when "a" then gets deleted?
2043 * "b.c" is left hanging around without data or children. This condition
2044 * is actually pretty easy to detect, but ... should it really be removed?
2045 * Is a chain pointing to it? An iterator? Who knows! (Note that the
2046 * references structure member cannot be looked at because it is private to
2047 * rbtdb.) This is ugly and makes me unhappy, but after hours of trying to
2048 * make it more aesthetically proper and getting nowhere, this is the way it
2049 * is going to stay until such time as it proves to be a *real* problem.
2050 *
2051 * Finally, for reference, note that the original routine that did node
2052 * joining was called join_nodes(). It has been excised, living now only
2053 * in the CVS history, but comments have been left behind that point to it just
2054 * in case someone wants to muck with this some more.
2055 *
2056 * The one positive aspect of all of this is that joining used to have a
2057 * case where it might fail. Without trying to join, now this function always
2058 * succeeds. It still returns isc_result_t, though, so the API wouldn't change.
2059 */
2060isc_result_t
2061dns_rbt_deletenode(dns_rbt_t *rbt, dns_rbtnode_t *node, bool recurse)
2062{
2063 dns_rbtnode_t *parent;
2064
2065 REQUIRE(VALID_RBT(rbt));
2066 REQUIRE(DNS_RBTNODE_VALID(node));
2067 INSIST(rbt->nodecount != 0);
2068
2069 if (DOWN(node) != NULL) {
2070 if (recurse) {
2071 PARENT(DOWN(node)) = NULL;
2072 deletetreeflat(rbt, 0, true, &DOWN(node));
2073 } else {
2074 if (DATA(node) != NULL && rbt->data_deleter != NULL)
2075 rbt->data_deleter(DATA(node), rbt->deleter_arg);
2076 DATA(node) = NULL;
2077
2078 /*
2079 * Since there is at least one node below this one and
2080 * no recursion was requested, the deletion is
2081 * complete. The down node from this node might be all
2082 * by itself on a single level, so join_nodes() could
2083 * be used to collapse the tree (with all the caveats
2084 * of the comment at the start of this function).
2085 * But join_nodes() function has now been removed.
2086 */
2087 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2088 }
2089 }
2090
2091 /*
2092 * Note the node that points to the level of the node
2093 * that is being deleted. If the deleted node is the
2094 * top level, parent will be set to NULL.
2095 */
2096 parent = get_upper_node(node);
2097
2098 /*
2099 * This node now has no down pointer, so now it needs
2100 * to be removed from this level.
2101 */
2102 deletefromlevel(node, parent == NULL ? &rbt->root : &DOWN(parent));
2103
2104 if (DATA(node) != NULL && rbt->data_deleter != NULL)
2105 rbt->data_deleter(DATA(node), rbt->deleter_arg);
2106
2107 unhash_node(rbt, node);
2108#if DNS_RBT_USEMAGIC

2294/*
2295 * Rebuild the hashtable to reduce the load factor
2296 */
2297static void
2298rehash(dns_rbt_t *rbt, unsigned int newcount) {
2299 unsigned int oldsize;
2300 dns_rbtnode_t **oldtable;
2301 dns_rbtnode_t *node;
2302 dns_rbtnode_t *nextnode;
2303 unsigned int hash;
2304 unsigned int i;
2305
2306 oldsize = (unsigned int)rbt->hashsize;
2307 oldtable = rbt->hashtable;
2308 do {
2309 INSIST((rbt->hashsize * 2 + 1) > rbt->hashsize);
2310 rbt->hashsize = rbt->hashsize * 2 + 1;
2311 } while (newcount >= (rbt->hashsize * 3));
2312 rbt->hashtable = isc_mem_get(rbt->mctx,
2313 rbt->hashsize * sizeof(dns_rbtnode_t *));
2314 if (rbt->hashtable == NULL) {
2315 rbt->hashtable = oldtable;
2316 rbt->hashsize = oldsize;
2317 return;
2318 }
2319
2320 for (i = 0; i < rbt->hashsize; i++)
2321 rbt->hashtable[i] = NULL;
2322
2323 for (i = 0; i < oldsize; i++) {
2324 for (node = oldtable[i]; node != NULL; node = nextnode) {
2325 hash = HASHVAL(node) % rbt->hashsize;
2326 nextnode = HASHNEXT(node);
2327 HASHNEXT(node) = rbt->hashtable[hash];
2328 rbt->hashtable[hash] = node;
2329 }
2330 }
2331
2332 isc_mem_put(rbt->mctx, oldtable, oldsize * sizeof(dns_rbtnode_t *));
2333}

2337 * rises above a critical level.
2338 */
2339static inline void
2340hash_node(dns_rbt_t *rbt, dns_rbtnode_t *node, const dns_name_t *name) {

2342
2343 if (rbt->nodecount >= (rbt->hashsize * 3))
2344 rehash(rbt, rbt->nodecount);

2346 hash_add_node(rbt, node, name);

2349/*
2350 * Remove a node from the hash table
2351 */
2352static inline void
2353unhash_node(dns_rbt_t *rbt, dns_rbtnode_t *node) {
2354 unsigned int bucket;
2355 dns_rbtnode_t *bucket_node;
2356
2357 REQUIRE(DNS_RBTNODE_VALID(node));
2358
2359 bucket = HASHVAL(node) % rbt->hashsize;
2360 bucket_node = rbt->hashtable[bucket];
2361
2362 if (bucket_node == node) {
2363 rbt->hashtable[bucket] = HASHNEXT(node);
2364 } else {
2365 while (HASHNEXT(bucket_node) != node) {
2366 INSIST(HASHNEXT(bucket_node) != NULL);
2367 bucket_node = HASHNEXT(bucket_node);
2368 }
2369 HASHNEXT(bucket_node) = HASHNEXT(node);
2370 }
2371}

2373static inline void
2374rotate_left(dns_rbtnode_t *node, dns_rbtnode_t **rootp) {
2375 dns_rbtnode_t *child;
2376
2377 REQUIRE(DNS_RBTNODE_VALID(node));
2378 REQUIRE(rootp != NULL);
2379
2380 child = RIGHT(node);
2381 INSIST(child != NULL);
2382
2383 RIGHT(node) = LEFT(child);
2384 if (LEFT(child) != NULL)
2385 PARENT(LEFT(child)) = node;
2386 LEFT(child) = node;
2387
2388 PARENT(child) = PARENT(node);
2389
2390 if (IS_ROOT(node)) {
2391 *rootp = child;
2392 child->is_root = 1;
2393 node->is_root = 0;
2394
2395 } else {
2396 if (LEFT(PARENT(node)) == node)
2397 LEFT(PARENT(node)) = child;
2398 else
2399 RIGHT(PARENT(node)) = child;
2400 }
2401
2402 PARENT(node) = child;
2403}

2427 } else {

2431 RIGHT(PARENT(node)) = child;

2437/*
2438 * This is the real workhorse of the insertion code, because it does the
2439 * true red/black tree on a single level.
2440 */
2441static void
2442addonlevel(dns_rbtnode_t *node, dns_rbtnode_t *current, int order,
2443 dns_rbtnode_t **rootp)
2444{
2445 dns_rbtnode_t *child, *root, *parent, *grandparent;
2446 dns_name_t add_name, current_name;
2447 dns_offsets_t add_offsets, current_offsets;
2448
2449 REQUIRE(rootp != NULL);
2450 REQUIRE(DNS_RBTNODE_VALID(node) && LEFT(node) == NULL &&
2451 RIGHT(node) == NULL);
2452 REQUIRE(current != NULL);
2453
2454 root = *rootp;
2455 if (root == NULL) {
2456 /*
2457 * First node of a level.
2458 */
2459 MAKE_BLACK(node);
2460 node->is_root = 1;
2461 PARENT(node) = current;
2462 *rootp = node;
2463 return;
2464 }
2465
2466 child = root;
2467 POST(child);
2468
2469 dns_name_init(&add_name, add_offsets);
2470 NODENAME(node, &add_name);
2471
2472 dns_name_init(&current_name, current_offsets);
2473 NODENAME(current, &current_name);
2474
2475 if (order < 0) {
2476 INSIST(LEFT(current) == NULL);
2477 LEFT(current) = node;
2478 } else {
2479 INSIST(RIGHT(current) == NULL);
2480 RIGHT(current) = node;
2481 }
2482
2483 INSIST(PARENT(node) == NULL);
2484 PARENT(node) = current;
2485
2486 MAKE_RED(node);
2487
2488 while (node != root && IS_RED(PARENT(node))) {
2489 /*
2490 * XXXDCL could do away with separate parent and grandparent
2491 * variables. They are vestiges of the days before parent
2492 * pointers. However, they make the code a little clearer.
2493 */
2494
2495 parent = PARENT(node);
2496 grandparent = PARENT(parent);
2497
2498 if (parent == LEFT(grandparent)) {
2499 child = RIGHT(grandparent);
2500 if (child != NULL && IS_RED(child)) {
2501 MAKE_BLACK(parent);
2502 MAKE_BLACK(child);
2503 MAKE_RED(grandparent);
2504 node = grandparent;
2505 } else {
2506 if (node == RIGHT(parent)) {
2507 rotate_left(parent, &root);
2508 node = parent;
2509 parent = PARENT(node);
2510 grandparent = PARENT(parent);
2511 }
2512 MAKE_BLACK(parent);
2513 MAKE_RED(grandparent);
2514 rotate_right(grandparent, &root);
2515 }
2516 } else {
2517 child = LEFT(grandparent);
2518 if (child != NULL && IS_RED(child)) {
2519 MAKE_BLACK(parent);
2520 MAKE_BLACK(child);
2521 MAKE_RED(grandparent);
2522 node = grandparent;
2523 } else {
2524 if (node == LEFT(parent)) {
2525 rotate_right(parent, &root);
2526 node = parent;
2527 parent = PARENT(node);
2528 grandparent = PARENT(parent);
2529 }
2530 MAKE_BLACK(parent);
2531 MAKE_RED(grandparent);
2532 rotate_left(grandparent, &root);
2533 }
2534 }
2535 }
2536
2537 MAKE_BLACK(root);
2538 ENSURE(IS_ROOT(root));
2539 *rootp = root;
2540
2541 return;
2542}

2544/*
2545 * This is the real workhorse of the deletion code, because it does the
2546 * true red/black tree on a single level.
2547 */
2548static void
2549deletefromlevel(dns_rbtnode_t *item, dns_rbtnode_t **rootp) {
2550 dns_rbtnode_t *child, *sibling, *parent;
2551 dns_rbtnode_t *successor;
2552
2553 REQUIRE(item != NULL);
2554
2555 /*
2556 * Verify that the parent history is (apparently) correct.
2557 */
2558 INSIST((IS_ROOT(item) && *rootp == item) ||
2559 (! IS_ROOT(item) &&
2560 (LEFT(PARENT(item)) == item ||
2561 RIGHT(PARENT(item)) == item)));
2562
2563 child = NULL;
2564
2565 if (LEFT(item) == NULL) {
2566 if (RIGHT(item) == NULL) {
2567 if (IS_ROOT(item)) {
2568 /*
2569 * This is the only item in the tree.
2570 */
2571 *rootp = NULL;
2572 return;
2573 }
2574 } else
2575 /*
2576 * This node has one child, on the right.
2577 */
2578 child = RIGHT(item);
2579
2580 } else if (RIGHT(item) == NULL)
2581 /*
2582 * This node has one child, on the left.
2583 */
2584 child = LEFT(item);
2585 else {
2586 dns_rbtnode_t holder, *tmp = &holder;
2587
2588 /*
2589 * This node has two children, so it cannot be directly
2590 * deleted. Find its immediate in-order successor and
2591 * move it to this location, then do the deletion at the
2592 * old site of the successor.
2593 */
2594 successor = RIGHT(item);
2595 while (LEFT(successor) != NULL)
2596 successor = LEFT(successor);
2597
2598 /*
2599 * The successor cannot possibly have a left child;
2600 * if there is any child, it is on the right.
2601 */
2602 if (RIGHT(successor) != NULL)
2603 child = RIGHT(successor);
2604
2605 /*
2606 * Swap the two nodes; it would be simpler to just replace
2607 * the value being deleted with that of the successor,
2608 * but this rigamarole is done so the caller has complete
2609 * control over the pointers (and memory allocation) of
2610 * all of nodes. If just the key value were removed from
2611 * the tree, the pointer to the node would be unchanged.
2612 */
2613
2614 /*
2615 * First, put the successor in the tree location of the
2616 * node to be deleted. Save its existing tree pointer
2617 * information, which will be needed when linking up
2618 * delete to the successor's old location.
2619 */
2620 memmove(tmp, successor, sizeof(dns_rbtnode_t));
2621
2622 if (IS_ROOT(item)) {
2623 *rootp = successor;
2624 successor->is_root = true;
2625 item->is_root = false;
2626
2627 } else
2628 if (LEFT(PARENT(item)) == item)
2629 LEFT(PARENT(item)) = successor;
2630 else
2631 RIGHT(PARENT(item)) = successor;
2632
2633 PARENT(successor) = PARENT(item);
2634 LEFT(successor) = LEFT(item);
2635 RIGHT(successor) = RIGHT(item);
2636 COLOR(successor) = COLOR(item);
2637
2638 if (LEFT(successor) != NULL)
2639 PARENT(LEFT(successor)) = successor;
2640 if (RIGHT(successor) != successor)
2641 PARENT(RIGHT(successor)) = successor;
2642
2643 /*
2644 * Now relink the node to be deleted into the
2645 * successor's previous tree location. PARENT(tmp)
2646 * is the successor's original parent.
2647 */
2648 INSIST(! IS_ROOT(item));
2649
2650 if (PARENT(tmp) == item) {
2651 /*
2652 * Node being deleted was successor's parent.
2653 */
2654 RIGHT(successor) = item;
2655 PARENT(item) = successor;
2656
2657 } else {
2658 LEFT(PARENT(tmp)) = item;
2659 PARENT(item) = PARENT(tmp);
2660 }
2661
2662 /*
2663 * Original location of successor node has no left.
2664 */
2665 LEFT(item) = NULL;
2666 RIGHT(item) = RIGHT(tmp);
2667 COLOR(item) = COLOR(tmp);
2668 }
2669
2670 /*
2671 * Remove the node by removing the links from its parent.
2672 */
2673 if (! IS_ROOT(item)) {
2674 if (LEFT(PARENT(item)) == item)
2675 LEFT(PARENT(item)) = child;
2676 else
2677 RIGHT(PARENT(item)) = child;
2678
2679 if (child != NULL)
2680 PARENT(child) = PARENT(item);
2681
2682 } else {
2683 /*
2684 * This is the root being deleted, and at this point
2685 * it is known to have just one child.
2686 */
2687 *rootp = child;
2688 child->is_root = 1;
2689 PARENT(child) = PARENT(item);
2690 }
2691
2692 /*
2693 * Fix color violations.
2694 */
2695 if (IS_BLACK(item)) {
2696 parent = PARENT(item);
2697
2698 while (child != *rootp && IS_BLACK(child)) {
2699 INSIST(child == NULL || ! IS_ROOT(child));
2700
2701 if (LEFT(parent) == child) {
2702 sibling = RIGHT(parent);
2703
2704 if (IS_RED(sibling)) {
2705 MAKE_BLACK(sibling);
2706 MAKE_RED(parent);
2707 rotate_left(parent, rootp);
2708 sibling = RIGHT(parent);
2709 }
2710
2711 INSIST(sibling != NULL);
2712
2713 if (IS_BLACK(LEFT(sibling)) &&
2714 IS_BLACK(RIGHT(sibling))) {
2715 MAKE_RED(sibling);
2716 child = parent;
2717
2718 } else {
2719
2720 if (IS_BLACK(RIGHT(sibling))) {
2721 MAKE_BLACK(LEFT(sibling));
2722 MAKE_RED(sibling);
2723 rotate_right(sibling, rootp);
2724 sibling = RIGHT(parent);
2725 }
2726
2727 COLOR(sibling) = COLOR(parent);
2728 MAKE_BLACK(parent);
2729 INSIST(RIGHT(sibling) != NULL);
2730 MAKE_BLACK(RIGHT(sibling));
2731 rotate_left(parent, rootp);
2732 child = *rootp;
2733 }
2734
2735 } else {
2736 /*
2737 * Child is parent's right child.
2738 * Everything is done the same as above,
2739 * except mirrored.
2740 */
2741 sibling = LEFT(parent);
2742
2743 if (IS_RED(sibling)) {
2744 MAKE_BLACK(sibling);
2745 MAKE_RED(parent);
2746 rotate_right(parent, rootp);
2747 sibling = LEFT(parent);
2748 }
2749
2750 INSIST(sibling != NULL);
2751
2752 if (IS_BLACK(LEFT(sibling)) &&
2753 IS_BLACK(RIGHT(sibling))) {
2754 MAKE_RED(sibling);
2755 child = parent;
2756
2757 } else {
2758 if (IS_BLACK(LEFT(sibling))) {
2759 MAKE_BLACK(RIGHT(sibling));
2760 MAKE_RED(sibling);
2761 rotate_left(sibling, rootp);
2762 sibling = LEFT(parent);
2763 }
2764
2765 COLOR(sibling) = COLOR(parent);
2766 MAKE_BLACK(parent);
2767 INSIST(LEFT(sibling) != NULL);
2768 MAKE_BLACK(LEFT(sibling));
2769 rotate_right(parent, rootp);
2770 child = *rootp;
2771 }
2772 }
2773
2774 parent = PARENT(child);
2775 }
2776
2777 if (IS_RED(child))
2778 MAKE_BLACK(child);
2779 }
2780}

2794static void
2795deletetreeflat(dns_rbt_t *rbt, unsigned int quantum, bool unhash,
2796 dns_rbtnode_t **nodep)
2797{
2798 dns_rbtnode_t *root = *nodep;
2799
2800 while (root != NULL) {
2801 /*
2802 * If there is a left, right or down node, walk into it
2803 * and iterate.
2804 */
2805 if (LEFT(root) != NULL) {
2806 dns_rbtnode_t *node = root;
2807 root = LEFT(root);
2808 LEFT(node) = NULL;
2809 } else if (RIGHT(root) != NULL) {
2810 dns_rbtnode_t *node = root;
2811 root = RIGHT(root);
2812 RIGHT(node) = NULL;
2813 } else if (DOWN(root) != NULL) {
2814 dns_rbtnode_t *node = root;
2815 root = DOWN(root);
2816 DOWN(node) = NULL;
2817 } else {
2818 /*
2819 * There are no left, right or down nodes, so we
2820 * can free this one and go back to its parent.
2821 */
2822 dns_rbtnode_t *node = root;
2823 root = PARENT(root);
2824
2825 if (DATA(node) != NULL && rbt->data_deleter != NULL)
2826 rbt->data_deleter(DATA(node),
2827 rbt->deleter_arg);
2828 if (unhash)
2829 unhash_node(rbt, node);
2830 /*
2831 * Note: we don't call unhash_node() here as we
2832 * are destroying the complete RBT tree.
2833 */
2834#if DNS_RBT_USEMAGIC
2835 node->magic = 0;
2836#endif
2837 freenode(rbt, &node);
2838 if (quantum != 0 && --quantum == 0)
2839 break;
2840 }
2841 }
2842
2843 *nodep = root;
2844}

2846static size_t
2847getheight_helper(dns_rbtnode_t *node) {
2848 size_t dl, dr;

2868static bool
2869check_properties_helper(dns_rbtnode_t *node) {
2870 if (node == NULL)
2871 return (true);
2872
2873 if (IS_RED(node)) {
2874 /* Root nodes must be BLACK. */
2875 if (IS_ROOT(node))
2876 return (false);
2877
2878 /* Both children of RED nodes must be BLACK. */
2879 if (IS_RED(LEFT(node)) || IS_RED(RIGHT(node)))
2880 return (false);
2881 }
2882
2883 if ((DOWN(node) != NULL) && (!IS_ROOT(DOWN(node))))
2884 return (false);
2885
2886 if (IS_ROOT(node)) {
2887 if ((PARENT(node) != NULL) &&
2888 (DOWN(PARENT(node)) != node))
2889 return (false);
2890
2891 if (get_upper_node(node) != PARENT(node))
2892 return (false);
2893 }
2894
2895 /* If node is assigned to the down_ pointer of its parent, it is
2896 * a subtree root and must have the flag set.
2897 */
2898 if (((!PARENT(node)) ||
2899 (DOWN(PARENT(node)) == node)) &&
2900 (!IS_ROOT(node)))
2901 {
2902 return (false);
2903 }
2904
2905 /* Repeat tests with this node's children. */
2906 return (check_properties_helper(LEFT(node)) &&
2907 check_properties_helper(RIGHT(node)) &&
2908 check_properties_helper(DOWN(node)));
2909}
2910
2911static bool
2912check_black_distance_helper(dns_rbtnode_t *node, size_t *distance) {
2913 size_t dl, dr, dd;
2914
2915 if (node == NULL) {
2916 *distance = 1;
2917 return (true);
2918 }
2919
2920 if (!check_black_distance_helper(LEFT(node), &dl))
2921 return (false);
2922
2923 if (!check_black_distance_helper(RIGHT(node), &dr))
2924 return (false);
2925
2926 if (!check_black_distance_helper(DOWN(node), &dd))
2927 return (false);
2928
2929 /* Left and right side black node counts must match. */
2930 if (dl != dr)
2931 return (false);
2932
2933 if (IS_BLACK(node))
2934 dl++;
2935
2936 *distance = dl;
2937
2938 return (true);
2939}

2941bool
2942dns__rbt_checkproperties(dns_rbt_t *rbt) {
2943 size_t dd;
2944
2945 if (!check_properties_helper(rbt->root))
2946 return (false);
2947
2948 /* Path from a given node to all its leaves must contain the
2949 * same number of BLACK child nodes. This is done separately
2950 * here instead of inside check_properties_helper() as
2951 * it would take (n log n) complexity otherwise.
2952 */
2953 return (check_black_distance_helper(rbt->root, &dd));
2954}

3200isc_result_t
3201dns_rbtnodechain_prev(dns_rbtnodechain_t *chain, dns_name_t *name,
3202 dns_name_t *origin)
3203{
3204 dns_rbtnode_t *current, *previous, *predecessor;
3205 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
3206 bool new_origin = false;
3207
3208 REQUIRE(VALID_CHAIN(chain) && chain->end != NULL);
3209
3210 predecessor = NULL;
3211
3212 current = chain->end;
3213
3214 if (LEFT(current) != NULL) {
3215 /*
3216 * Moving left one then right as far as possible is the
3217 * previous node, at least for this level.
3218 */
3219 current = LEFT(current);
3220
3221 while (RIGHT(current) != NULL)
3222 current = RIGHT(current);
3223
3224 predecessor = current;
3225
3226 } else {
3227 /*
3228 * No left links, so move toward the root. If at any point on
3229 * the way there the link from parent to child is a right
3230 * link, then the parent is the previous node, at least
3231 * for this level.
3232 */
3233 while (! IS_ROOT(current)) {
3234 previous = current;
3235 current = PARENT(current);
3236
3237 if (RIGHT(current) == previous) {
3238 predecessor = current;
3239 break;
3240 }
3241 }
3242 }
3243
3244 if (predecessor != NULL) {
3245 /*
3246 * Found a predecessor node in this level. It might not
3247 * really be the predecessor, however.
3248 */
3249 if (DOWN(predecessor) != NULL) {
3250 /*
3251 * The predecessor is really down at least one level.
3252 * Go down and as far right as possible, and repeat
3253 * as long as the rightmost node has a down pointer.
3254 */
3255 do {
3256 /*
3257 * XXX DCL Need to do something about origins
3258 * here. See whether to go down, and if so
3259 * whether it is truly what Bob calls a
3260 * new origin.
3261 */
3262 ADD_LEVEL(chain, predecessor);
3263 predecessor = DOWN(predecessor);
3264
3265 /* XXX DCL duplicated from above; clever
3266 * way to unduplicate? */
3267
3268 while (RIGHT(predecessor) != NULL)
3269 predecessor = RIGHT(predecessor);
3270 } while (DOWN(predecessor) != NULL);
3271
3272 /* XXX DCL probably needs work on the concept */
3273 if (origin != NULL)
3274 new_origin = true;
3275 }
3276
3277 } else if (chain->level_count > 0) {
3278 /*
3279 * Dang, didn't find a predecessor in this level.
3280 * Got to the root of this level without having traversed
3281 * any right links. Ascend the tree one level; the
3282 * node that points to this tree is the predecessor.
3283 */
3284 INSIST(chain->level_count > 0 && IS_ROOT(current));
3285 predecessor = chain->levels[--chain->level_count];
3286
3287 /* XXX DCL probably needs work on the concept */
3288 /*
3289 * Don't declare an origin change when the new origin is "."
3290 * at the top level tree, because "." is declared as the origin
3291 * for the second level tree.
3292 */
3293 if (origin != NULL &&
3294 (chain->level_count > 0 || OFFSETLEN(predecessor) > 1))
3295 new_origin = true;
3296 }
3297
3298 if (predecessor != NULL) {
3299 chain->end = predecessor;
3300
3301 if (new_origin) {
3302 result = dns_rbtnodechain_current(chain, name, origin,
3303 NULL);
3304 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3305 result = DNS_R_NEWORIGIN;
3306
3307 } else
3308 result = dns_rbtnodechain_current(chain, name, NULL,
3309 NULL);
3310
3311 } else
3312 result = ISC_R_NOMORE;
3313
3314 return (result);
3315}

3318dns_rbtnodechain_down(dns_rbtnodechain_t *chain, dns_name_t *name,
3319 dns_name_t *origin)
3320{
3321 dns_rbtnode_t *current, *successor;
3322 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
3323 bool new_origin = false;
3324
3325 REQUIRE(VALID_CHAIN(chain) && chain->end != NULL);
3326
3327 successor = NULL;
3328
3329 current = chain->end;
3330
3331 if (DOWN(current) != NULL) {
3332 /*

3335 * as the origin for the top level tree.

3338 OFFSETLEN(current) > 1)
3339 new_origin = true;
3340
3341 ADD_LEVEL(chain, current);
3342 current = DOWN(current);
3343

3345 current = LEFT(current);
3346

3424isc_result_t
3425dns_rbtnodechain_next(dns_rbtnodechain_t *chain, dns_name_t *name,
3426 dns_name_t *origin)
3427{
3428 dns_rbtnode_t *current, *previous, *successor;
3429 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
3430 bool new_origin = false;
3431
3432 REQUIRE(VALID_CHAIN(chain) && chain->end != NULL);
3433
3434 successor = NULL;
3435
3436 current = chain->end;
3437
3438 /*
3439 * If there is a level below this node, the next node is the leftmost
3440 * node of the next level.
3441 */
3442 if (DOWN(current) != NULL) {
3443 /*
3444 * Don't declare an origin change when the new origin is "."
3445 * at the second level tree, because "." is already declared
3446 * as the origin for the top level tree.
3447 */
3448 if (chain->level_count > 0 ||
3449 OFFSETLEN(current) > 1)
3450 new_origin = true;
3451
3452 ADD_LEVEL(chain, current);
3453 current = DOWN(current);
3454
3455 while (LEFT(current) != NULL)
3456 current = LEFT(current);
3457
3458 successor = current;
3459
3460 } else if (RIGHT(current) == NULL) {
3461 /*
3462 * The successor is up, either in this level or a previous one.
3463 * Head back toward the root of the tree, looking for any path
3464 * that was via a left link; the successor is the node that has
3465 * that left link. In the event the root of the level is
3466 * reached without having traversed any left links, ascend one
3467 * level and look for either a right link off the point of
3468 * ascent, or search for a left link upward again, repeating
3469 * ascends until either case is true.
3470 */
3471 do {
3472 while (! IS_ROOT(current)) {
3473 previous = current;
3474 current = PARENT(current);
3475
3476 if (LEFT(current) == previous) {
3477 successor = current;
3478 break;
3479 }
3480 }
3481
3482 if (successor == NULL) {
3483 /*
3484 * Reached the root without having traversed
3485 * any left pointers, so this level is done.
3486 */
3487 if (chain->level_count == 0) {
3488 /*
3489 * If the tree we are iterating over
3490 * was modified since this chain was
3491 * initialized in a way that caused
3492 * node splits to occur, "current" may
3493 * now be pointing to a root node which
3494 * appears to be at level 0, but still
3495 * has a parent. If that happens,
3496 * abort. Otherwise, we are done
3497 * looking for a successor as we really
3498 * reached the root node on level 0.
3499 */
3500 INSIST(PARENT(current) == NULL);
3501 break;
3502 }
3503
3504 current = chain->levels[--chain->level_count];
3505 new_origin = true;
3506
3507 if (RIGHT(current) != NULL)
3508 break;
3509 }
3510 } while (successor == NULL);
3511 }
3512
3513 if (successor == NULL && RIGHT(current) != NULL) {
3514 current = RIGHT(current);
3515
3516 while (LEFT(current) != NULL)
3517 current = LEFT(current);
3518
3519 successor = current;
3520 }
3521
3522 if (successor != NULL) {
3523 /*
3524 * If we determine that the current node is the successor to
3525 * itself, we will run into an infinite loop, so abort instead.
3526 */
3527 INSIST(chain->end != successor);
3528
3529 chain->end = successor;
3530
3531 /*
3532 * It is not necessary to use dns_rbtnodechain_current like
3533 * the other functions because this function will never
3534 * find a node in the topmost level. This is because the
3535 * root level will never be more than one name, and everything
3536 * in the megatree is a successor to that node, down at
3537 * the second level or below.
3538 */
3539
3540 if (name != NULL)
3541 NODENAME(chain->end, name);
3542
3543 if (new_origin) {
3544 if (origin != NULL)
3545 result = chain_name(chain, origin, false);
3546
3547 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
3548 result = DNS_R_NEWORIGIN;
3549
3550 } else
3551 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
3552
3553 } else
3554 result = ISC_R_NOMORE;
3555
3556 return (result);
3557}
